The article discusses a notice sent by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Federal Register, stating that the national emergency with respect to hostage-taking and the wrongful detention of United States nationals abroad will continue beyond July 19, 2023. The President emphasizes that hostage-taking and wrongful detention undermine the rule of law and pose a threat to the international political system and the safety of US nationals and others abroad. Therefore, the President has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency. The notice was sent in accordance with Section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act, which requires the President to publish a notice in the Federal Register and transmit it to Congress within 90 days prior to the anniversary date of the emergency declaration.